>   51: \subsection{Multi-label Causal Discovery}\label{c7:section:multi_label_cd}
    52: Multi-label causal discovery seeks to identify the Markov Boundary or \(\mathcal{MB}\) (Def.~\ref{def:markov_boundary}) of each label, i.e., its minimal set of parents, children, and spouses—such that the label is conditionally independent of all other variables given its \(\mathcal{MB}\) \cite{optimal_feature_set_cd}. This boundary constitutes an optimal feature set for tasks such as explainable modeling and feature selection under the faithfulness assumption.

