> 1467: %\paragraph{Enumerating all CI-tests}
  1468: In contrary to the sample-level multi-label causal discovery case, for each time step \(t\) we must perform \(t\) CI-tests (one for every potential lag per step). For a sequence of length \(L\), the total number of CI-tests is given by \(\sum^L_{t=1} t = \frac{L(L+1)}{2}\) which grows quadratically with the sequence length. As a result, even on multiple GPUs, inference becomes computationally intractable.

