   433: We now consider simulations with the exponential intervention $\varphi(t)=e^{-0.2t}$. As Figure \ref{fig:cir_exp} illustrates, the transmission rate $\beta_t = \varphi(t)P_t^C$ decays rapidly enough to ensure the integrated intensity process $H_t$ remains a.s. finite. This creates a ``continuous curbing effect'', preventing the eventual infection of the entire population.

