   309: 
>  310: % \paragraph{Immersion/QoE calculation: what is optimized?}
   311: % Recent works quantify Metaverse experience using QoE-style metrics and attention-aware perception terms. For example, \cite{refeig} proposes \emph{Meta-Immersion} by combining objective URLLC KPIs with attention-weighted rendering quality, while \cite{refelven,9999298} study QoE/attention-aware experience modeling from a network-centric viewpoint. These works directly motivate CIVIC’s immersion-centric objective; however, CIVIC’s immersion model is explicitly \emph{VE--DT coupled}, i.e., it integrates VE perceptual quality together with DT fidelity components (structural/behavioral/temporal) rather than treating DT synchronization as a separate objective.

- file: sample\arxiv_sources\2604.02284v1\rigor_test.tex (line 313)
  error: Immersion-driven resource allocation: how is immersion achieved under constraints?
  message: Should this be "Immersion-Driven Resource Allocation: How Is Immersion Achieved Under Constraints?"? Follow your preferred style guide and register as an exception if necessary.
   312: 
>  313: % \paragraph{Immersion-driven resource allocation: how is immersion achieved under constraints?}
   314: % Given a QoE/immersion target, most related works optimize a \emph{subset} of resources and decisions. On the streaming/rendering side, FoV-aware control and robust tile selection improve QoE under limited bandwidth \cite{10294071}, and constrained learning approaches target QoE tradeoffs such as delay versus video quality \cite{reftwenyfour}. On the edge/offloading side, MEC-based prediction/association improves long-term VR QoE \cite{reftweelve}, multi-objective learning trades immersion against device energy \cite{feng2024resource}, and application-level frameworks allocate multi-tier resources via admission/placement decisions \cite{chu2024dynamic,aaa}. These directions connect to CIVIC’s provisioning problem; nevertheless, CIVIC differs in two key ways: (i) it jointly allocates \emph{VE and DT resources} to directly maximize the holistic immersion objective, and (ii) it targets a \emph{multi-MSP setting} where provisioning decisions must remain feasible under decentralized budgets.

- file: sample\arxiv_sources\2604.02284v1\rigor_test.tex (line 316)
