  message: Should this be "Why Cooperation Matters: Beyond Single-Provider Optimization."? Follow your preferred style guide and register as an exception if necessary.
   315: 
>  316: % \paragraph{Why cooperation matters: beyond single-provider optimization.}
   317: % Some works introduce incentives/markets to improve efficiency of allocating rendering/VR services \cite{9838736,liu2025cooperativevr}, and DT-focused efforts optimize freshness/energy (e.g., AoI-energy tradeoffs) \cite{guo2024aoi_dt}. These ideas are complementary, but they do not provide an integrated mechanism that (a) explicitly optimizes \emph{immersion as VE--DT coupled experience} and (b) enables \emph{cross-MSP resilience} when individual MSPs face local resource scarcity. CIVIC fills this gap by combining an immersion-driven allocation objective with a cooperative \emph{credit-sharing} control plane across MSPs, allowing budgets/resources to be redistributed while preserving immersion thresholds.

