  2257: 
> 2258: \paragraph{Inference algorithms.}
  2259: We compute (i) a MAP estimate by gradient-based optimization of the negative log-posterior and (ii) posterior samples using the No-U-Turn Sampler (NUTS), i.e.\ an adaptive Hamiltonian Monte Carlo scheme, in the $d_Z$-dimensional latent space. Because $d_Z=16 \ll p=784$, NUTS can be applied in latent space even though the unknown field is high-dimensional and each log-posterior evaluation requires a PDE solve. We compare against two baselines: a TV-regularized MAP estimate in pixel space and an unconditional deep-prior baseline implemented as an unconditional VAE with $z\sim \mathcal{N}(0,I)$. For both deep priors we report MAP and posterior-mean reconstructions.

