>  173: \paragraph{Generation settings.} In the \emph{self-generated} setting, given a prompt $q$, we generate $a$ from $M_\theta$ and then $u$ from the same model under the user role (Eq.~\ref{eq:user-turn}). In the \emph{held-out} setting, used for post-training transfer checks and judge validation, we remove the final user turn from multi-turn conversations and ask the model to generate under the user role. All generation uses \emph{vLLM}\footnote{Our generations can be verified with \href{https://hub.docker.com/layers/verlai/verl/vllm017.latest/}{verlai/verl:vllm017.latest} docker image. We made use of H200 gpus for all experiments.} with modified chat templates that permit user-role continuation. We primarily use temperature~$0$ (deterministic/greedy) generation; additional sampled generations ($T \in \{0.3, 0.7, 1.0\}$) probe whether interaction awareness is present in a model's broader distribution (\S\ref{sec:temperature-results}).
