>  328: \paragraph{Explicit question.} Table~\ref{tab:perturbations}~(Right) shows the complementary perturbation on the instruction-following datasets. \texttt{gpt-oss-120b} shows the strongest response: genuine follow-up jumps from $1.3\%$ to $25.7\%$ on IFBench, with $99.0\%$ of user turns changing text. \texttt{gpt-oss-20b} follows at smaller magnitude ($1.0\% \to 6.0\%$). \texttt{GLM-4.7} changes $99\%$ of its user turns but genuine follow-up barely increases ($4.7\% \to 5.0\%$ on IFBench). Qwen models again show low sensitivity: \texttt{Qwen3.5-27B} changes only $6.3\%$ of turns, and \texttt{Qwen3.5-397B-A17B} \emph{decreases} in genuine follow-up ($7.7\% \to 4.7\%$ on IFBench), suggesting the perturbation disrupts its existing follow-up behavior rather than eliciting new responses.
