>  584: \paragraph{Annotation protocol.} We constructed multiple 100-example annotation packets sampled from the full evaluation panel. Each packet was drawn as a random sample from the mix of all datasets used in the paper. We constructed two types of packets: \emph{hard-case} packets built from \texttt{nano} versus \texttt{gpt-5.4} disagreements plus judge-agree genuine and judge-agree nongenuine examples, and \emph{natural-prevalence} packets sampled proportionally from the full \texttt{nano} versus \texttt{mini} panel. Packets were distributed to peer AI researchers with expertise in LLMs; we obtained $5$ completed annotation returns.
   585: 

